Supermarkets General Corp saidit received an unsolicited proposal from a third party toacquire the company at 41.75 dlrs per share in cash.    Supermarkets also said it retained Shearson Lehman BrothersInc to advise its board of directors on the proposal.    Supermarkets General currently has about 38.5 mln sharesoutstanding.    Its stock is currently trading at 34-1/4 on the New YorkStock Exchange.    The Woodbridge, N.J., supermarket operator of over 180supermarkets and other specialty retail stores, conveniencefood stores and drug stores.    For the nine months ended November 30, Supermarketsreported net income of 41.7 mln dlrs.    Reuter&#3;